This is a known breaking change. Android 15 (API 35) enforces **edge-to-edge** display, so `SOFT_INPUT_ADJUST_RESIZE` (which `WindowSoftInputModeAdjust.Resize` mapped to) is now ignored. The window no longer physically resizes — instead you must react to **IME insets**.

## Fix: Listen to keyboard insets on Android

In your `Platforms/Android/MainActivity.cs`:

```csharp
using Android.Views;
using AndroidX.Core.View;
using Microsoft.Maui.Platform;

public class MainActivity : MauiAppCompatActivity
{
    protected override void OnCreate(Bundle? savedInstanceState)
    {
        base.OnCreate(savedInstanceState);

        // Keep AdjustResize — it still triggers inset changes,
        // it just no longer shrinks the window.
        Window!.SetSoftInputMode(SoftInput.AdjustResize);

        // React to the keyboard (IME) inset
        var content = FindViewById(Android.Resource.Id.Content)!;
        ViewCompat.SetOnApplyWindowInsetsListener(content, new KeyboardInsetsListener());
    }

    private class KeyboardInsetsListener : Java.Lang.Object, IOnApplyWindowInsetsListener
    {
        public WindowInsetsCompat OnApplyWindowInsets(View view, WindowInsetsCompat insets)
        {
            var imeInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.Ime());
            var navInsets = insets.GetInsets(WindowInsetsCompat.Type.NavigationBars());

            // Use the larger of keyboard or nav-bar bottom inset
            int bottom = Math.Max(imeInsets.Bottom, navInsets.Bottom);
            view.SetPadding(0, 0, 0, bottom);

            return insets;
        }
    }
}
```

## XAML layout (chat screen)

```xml
<Grid RowDefinitions="*, Auto">
    <CollectionView Grid.Row="0" ItemsSource="{Binding Messages}" ... />

    <HorizontalStackLayout Grid.Row="1" Padding="8">
        <Entry Placeholder="Type a message..." HorizontalOptions="FillAndExpand" />
        <Button Text="Send" Command="{Binding SendCommand}" />
    </HorizontalStackLayout>
</Grid>
```

## Why this works

| .NET 9 (API ≤ 34) | .NET 10 (API 35+) |
|---|---|
| `AdjustResize` shrinks the window | Window stays full-screen (edge-to-edge) |
| Layout auto-adjusts | You get `IME` insets with the keyboard height |
| No extra code needed | Set bottom padding from the inset value |

The insets listener adds bottom padding equal to the keyboard height, pushing your input bar up — exactly like the old resize behavior.

**Tip:** If you only need a quick fix and don't need precise control, `SoftInput.AdjustPan` still works — it scrolls the entire view up so the focused field is visible. But for a chat UI where you want the message list to shrink and the input to stay anchored, the insets approach above is the right solution.
